Hierarchical Edge Bundling

Load packages

library(tidyverse)

# for networks:
library(igraph)
library(ggraph)

Create random data

It’s high time I learnt to create sample data!

To create a plot, we need the vertices. These are a dataframe with the unique values of from and to:

vertices <-data.frame(
    name = unique(c(hierarchy$to, hierarchy$from))
  )

vertices

Plot with igraph and ggraph:

Then, using ggraph:

mygraph %>%
  ggraph(
    layout = 'dendrogram',
    circular = F
  ) +
  geom_edge_link()


mygraph %>%
  ggraph(
    layout = 'dendrogram',
    circular = T
  ) +
  geom_edge_diagonal()
